The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on detecting lexical relations using distributional semantic models. This makes it highly likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of network measures suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of co-hyponymy detection also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and semantic integration (cs.SI), making these sub-categories likely as well.
